":"–8 juni 1320","–1320":"–1320","1251–1340":"1251–1340","1295–Female":"1295–Overleden","–Male":"Overleden","1221–Male":"1221–Overleden","8 June 1320":"8 juni 1320","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1221":"1221","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1251":"1251","about 1295":"circa 1295","Ashton, Devonshire, England":"Ashton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"en":{"–8 June 1320":"–8 June 1320","–1320":"–1320","1251–1340":"1251–1340","1295–Female":"1295–Deceased","–Male":"Deceased","1221–Male":"1221–Deceased","8 June 1320":"8 June 1320","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1221":"1221","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1251":"1251","about 1295":"about 1295","Ashton, Devonshire, England":"Ashton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hilion","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish:","patronymic meaning ‘son of <i>Hild</i>’; see   Hild   2.","patronymic meaning ‘son of <i>Hille</i>’; see   Hill   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Hillson","meanings":["English: variant of   Hilson  ."]},{"name":"Hild","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Erna, Inge, Irmgard, Johann, Udo, Volker.","German: from a short form of   Hildebrand   or other compound names with the same initial element, <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’.","English: from the Middle English female personal name <i>Hild</i> (of which <i>Hilda</i> is the Latin form), a short form of a compound name with the first element <i>Hild-</i>, e.g. ancient Germanic <i>Hildigard</i> or Old English <i>Hildgȳth</i>, from <i>hild</i> ‘strife, battle’. Compare   Hilliard  ."]}]},{"name":"Margarita","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of   Margaret  , now widely adopted in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[{"name":"Margaret","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":14,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":23,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":58,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Margarita de Hilion was born as the daughter of Robert III de Helion. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Sir Richard Le Prouz. She died on 8 June 1320, in Ashton, Devon, England."},"et":{"–8 June 1320":"–8. juuni 1320","–1320":"–1320","1251–1340":"1251–1340","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1221–Male":"1221–Surnud","8 June 1320":"8. juuni 1320","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1221":"1221","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1251":"1251","about 1295":"umbes 1295","Ashton, Devonshire, England":"Ashton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"–8 June 1320":"–8. kesäkuuta 1320","–1320":"–1320","1251–1340":"1251–1340","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1221–Male":"1221–Kuollut","8 June 1320":"8. kesäkuuta 1320","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1221":"1221","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1251":"1251","about 1295":"noin 1295","Ashton, Devonshire, England":"Ashton, Devon, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"–8 June 1320":"–8 juin 1320","–1320":"–1320","1251–1340":"1251–1340","1295–Female":"1295–Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1221–Male":"1221–Décédé","8 June 1320":"8 juin 1320","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1221":"1221","1320":"1320","1340":"1340","1295":"1295","1251":"1251","about 1295":"environ 1295","Ashton, Devonshire, England":"Ashton, Devon, Angleterre",